               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of donors in Texts I-3 and II; groups of lines on the incipit page of Texts I-1 and I-2b; incipit of all other texts, incipit of sections of Texts I-2b and II-2; section numbers of Text I-2b; titles of miracles written in the upper margin of Text I-2b; the word ʾǝsäggǝd "I worship" in Text II-1; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>All miracles of St. Mary are numbered.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I-3 includes the hymn:</note>
                     <note>- ʾƎsäggǝd läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Maryam Mariham ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali ... "I worship Thee, O my Lady, Holy Virgin Mary, Mother of Jesus Christ the Almighty ..." (fols. 10va-11va).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
