                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Hand a: mediocre. Hand b: mediocre. Hand c: poor and careless. Hand d: irregular.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (hands a and b: strong red, hand c: vivid red, hand d: vivid crimson).</seg>
                        <persName role="scribe" corresp="PRS00000">Wäldä Muse, ʾabunä</persName>Wäldä Muse is mentioned as the scribe of Texts I-1, I-2 and I-3 on fol. 8rb.<date>Second half of 19th century</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a (Wäldä Muse): 3ra-8rb (Texts I-1, I-2a). The handwriting appears hastily executed with right-sloping letters of angular shape. Some letters have forked hook vowel markers (e.g., በ, ኀ, ን, ገ) the vowel marker of እ is notably long. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
Hand b: 9ra-11va (Texts I-3). The script is characterized by angular, broadly spaced and irregularly slanted letters. Most of the letters have hairlines. The letter ለ is formed in a peculiar shape.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
Hand c: 12ra-91ra (Texts I-2b, I-4). The handwriting appears very uneven and irregular. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
Hand d: 92ra-120va (Text II). It is difficult to determine whether one or more scribes were involved in writing (cp. fols. 108rb, 109vb, 110vb).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2ra">Fol. 2ra</locus>: Note referring to commissioning or purchase of the Ms. (?)<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 2ra: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ [n.l. ኤል]፡ ዘተሣየጥዎ፡ በንዋየ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ወሊቆሙ፡ [n.l.]፡ ወካሕናቱሂ፡ [n.l.]፡ ዘአጽሐፋ፡ ለዘቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አበ፡ ጵኵሚስ፡ ትኵኖሙ፡ መድኀኒተ፡ ሥጋ፡ ወነፍስ፡ አመ፡ ይመጽአ፡ በዕለተ፡ ሐዲስ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ነግሥት፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in hand c; some words (names) have been erased. Its content is not quite clear. The note states that the book has been bought by a person probably called Täklä Mikaʾel (the same name might has been erased throughout the main text) with the church's money. The one who has commissioned the writing was ʾabba Ṗakwǝmis. The names of the abbot and priests have been erased.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#121v">Fol. 121v</locus>: Unidentified text referring to Jesus Christ.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The text is barely legible due to faded ink and erasures.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The scribe of Text II (hand d) often disregarded the ruling lines.&#xD;
- Titles of some miracles of St. Mary (until the 37th miracle, fol. 53) are written in the upper margins, in red.&#xD;
- Corrections are written over erasures: e.g., fols. 29vb, 35ra, 47rb, 77rb, 86vb. &#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names of St Mary or the donors are left unfilled: fols. 38va, 41rab, 48ra, 50va.&#xD;
- Crude ornamental bands: fols. 3r, 90rb, 91ra.&#xD;
- Scribbles: fol. 1v.</item>
                     </list>
